article.headline: Auburn 66, SE Louisiana 51
article.story: AUBURN, Ala. (AP) -- Frank Tolbert scored 13 points and Daniel Hayles added 11 to help lead Auburn to a 66-51 victory over Southeastern Louisiana Wednesday night. Auburn (4-2) took an early lead and held on to end the half with a 27-17 score. Tigers coach Jeff Lebo said a collision between Tolbert and teammate Ronny LeMelle while battling for a loose ball helped set the team's aggressive tone for the game. The two butted heads with 2:31 to play in the first and left the court bleeding, but returned in the second half. LeMelle received stitches after the game. "Ronny had a really good gash over his eye," Lebo said. "They went after it. Ronny will look like a real player now with a gash like that. Our two captains going after it set the tone for us." Daryl Cohen led the Lions (5-2) with 16 points, Ricky Woods followed with 12 points and seven rebounds and Quennell Greene added 11 points.
